node.text:
I used to give myself a LOT of credit for my marriage to @lisabilyeu. I thought, damn, man... I’m GOOD at this. And then it hit me... the statement that 80% of a successful relationship is selection. 

You have to choose the right partner. A high functioning relationship will be the greatest joy of your life - something well worth great sacrifice to protect and nurture. But a dysfunctional relationship will completely dismantle your life. 

Before you embark on the journey of rebuilding, make sure that you’re rebuilding the right relationship. If this is the right relationship - amazing! Go on in repairing. But, man... if it’s not. If you’re in a relationship with someone who has contempt for you or you have contempt for them, I advise you to face head on that this may not be the right relationship to save. 

Just keep in mind, your partner is looking at you the same way. You both have to be worth fighting for. 

For anyone out there struggling, I’m sending you good vibes and hoping that you can build a better situation for yourself - with your current partner or without them. 

But don’t think your worth is tied up in making it work. You’ve only got one shot at life, so make sure you’re building something that lifts you and those around you up. I’m sending all the love in the world. 

For @lisabilyeu ’s take on this be sure to subscribe to our Relationship Theory YouTube channel. We go deep on all of this stuff. Link in bio.

node.title: Is It Time To Dump Your Partner

node.text:
On this week’s episode of Health Theory, join me as I reveal the daily habits that help me perform at an elite level. 

If you have followed me for any amount of time, you have likely heard me say action cures all. Since starting Healthy Theory, I have interviewed over 90 specialists and experts about everything from brain cognition, to gut microbiome, to reverse aging. Information is meant to be put into action, so today I am sharing with you what my daily routine consists of at the moment. This episode is Health Theory In Action.

To watch the entire episode on your favorite platform, click the link in bio.

node.text:
I am not a born entrepreneur. What I am is relentless. At first I was relentless about making money which burned me out. Now, I am relentless about chasing FULFILLMENT, and it’s this pursuit, the dogged determination of finding and satiating my need to live a life worth living, that drives me every day. In shifting my focus I have been able to build massively successful companies, avoid burn out, and truly live! But it took me YEARS, no fucking joke, YEARS to get here. 

If you are looking to find fulfillment and get real results in your business I want to invite you to join my Business Decision Making Workshop. This is a 4-week intensive for anyone with a 6-figure+ business looking to take things to the next level and think differently about how they overcome their problems. This is the distillation of all the years I spent building businesses. It is the same rubric I use every day as I build Impact Theory. 

If you want to join, click the link in bio. It is time to make it happen!

node.text:
I used to give myself a LOT of credit for my marriage to @lisabilyeu. I thought, damn, man... I’m GOOD at this. And then it hit me... the statement that 80% of a successful relationship is selection. 

You have to choose the right partner. A high functioning relationship will be the greatest joy of your life - something well worth great sacrifice to protect and nurture. But a dysfunctional relationship will completely dismantle your life. 

Before you embark on the journey of rebuilding, make sure that you’re rebuilding the right relationship. If this is the right relationship - amazing! Go on in repairing. But, man... if it’s not. If you’re in a relationship with someone who has contempt for you or you have contempt for them, I advise you to face head on that this may not be the right relationship to save. 

Just keep in mind, your partner is looking at you the same way. You both have to be worth fighting for. 

For anyone out there struggling, I’m sending you good vibes and hoping that you can build a better situation for yourself - with your current partner or without them. 

But don’t think your worth is tied up in making it work. You’ve only got one shot at life, so make sure you’re building something that lifts you and those around you up. I’m sending all the love in the world. 

For @lisabilyeu ’s take on this be sure to subscribe to our Relationship Theory YouTube channel. We go deep on all of this stuff. Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Tom Bilyeu on July 31, 2021 tagging @tombilyeu. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: Now that we have that out in the open, what are you going to do about it? How will you take control of your life? No one is coming to save you, so it is on you!

Hindsight is 20/20, but successful people have excellent vision for the now and even better vision on the future. You must become extremely intentional with what you want your future to be! #ImpactTheoryUniversity

node.text: I love this quote so much, because it is so damn true. It's all about how you feel about yourself when you're by yourself. It's about service and falling in love with pushing yourself past the breaking point to get better every damn day. Ironically enough, fulfillment is born out of suffering with a purpose.

Stop scrolling and think. Think critically about all the things you just saw on Instagram. Probably a lot of people flaunting their stuff. Their fancy cars or houses or exotic vacations. What isn’t ever shown (cause it isn’t sexy or cool) is the work they had to do to get there.

Do not believe the lies. Success comes through work. HARD WORK.

If you are a 6 figure+ business owner looking to put in that hard work and scale your business, click the link in the bio and learn about my Business Decision-Making Workshop. I will teach you the skills and the thinking patterns I employ to radically grow my companies. Watch the video and then sign up for a call so one of my team can determine if this is right for you!

node.text:
Here's my best relationship advice - elevate your partner. You've got to want them to win. Relationships require a lot of sacrifices and unless on balance the relationship gives you far more than it takes, what's the point? Everyone has to be responsible for their own emotions and for their own growth, but having someone that makes you feel better about yourself and encourages you to go for broke is magical. So be sure to take time to celebrate and encourage them. Go way the hell out of your way to sincerely compliment them. Don't bullshit, but hone in on the good stuff. You will see more of whatever you focus on, so focus on the good stuff and say it out loud so the other person knows how you feel. 

To that end, I want to shout out my wife @lisabilyeu! Today is her birthday. Baby, I hope this day is awesome for you and you know how much you inspire me. You are an HCMF to be sure and I couldn't be more proud of you. Happy Birthday!!

📸 @Peter_Hurley

node.text:
One thing @lisabilyeu and I have learned is that communication is everything. It is literally going to determine the success or failure of your relationship. You have to define terms, develop keen self awareness, understand each other’s weaknesses, admit your insecurities, and much, much more. And above all of that, is getting good at the hard conversations. First of all, you have to be willing to say the truth, even when it’s the last thing you want to say. The reason is simple, without trust there is no real connection. Over time you will become isolated and resentful. The only way to avoid that fate is to tell the truth even when it means pissing off the other person. I can’t tell you the number of times I’ve been tempted to lie to Lisa because it would spare her feelings or end an argument. But I never do it because I don’t want to lose her trust. In the short term, lying is effective. But in the long term, it destroys. That’s why you’ve got to get good at the hard conversations. 

If you want to hear more depth on topics like this then go subscribe to our relationship channel on YouTube - Relationship Theory. Link in bio.
